title: For Sale:  Good condition Norinco SKS with crack to fore-end of stock
location: RTP/CH/Apex/Morrisville/Cary/Holly Springs, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Up for sale, a good condition Norinco SKS covered in cosmoline, untouched by me. I just don't have time to restore it. It has a crack to the fore-end of the stock and would make a great fixer upper, if you have time to glue it up and refinish it. Apart from the stock, the rifle is in great shape, rated as Good. They shoot great and are pretty accurate and are probably the best flavor of SKS around (light compared to the yugo, for example). If you did nothing to the stock, you could simply get a Tapco bayonet fit stock and do this up. It would be about an hour's worth of work at most. You could also just get a replacement wood stock and it would take five minutes to field strip and put it into a new stock. The current stock has some really interested flecking in the wood itself, kinda like quarter sawn oak ray fleck, it has a ribboning effect which is pretty attractive looking. It might be worth doing it up?

I can meet in RTP/CH/Apex/Morrisville/Cary/Holly Springs or Fuquay Varina only. My car isn't up to long drives. Sorry, I'm firm on price. If I don't sell this, I will just store it away and forget that I have it again.

title: For Sale:  NIB Para Ordinance 7.45 LDA Stainless 1911
postcontent:
While there are many firearms out there inspired by the 1911, the Para-Ordnance 7.45 LDA stands out from the crowd. The LDA refers to the 7.45's light double action trigger, a feature that differentiates it from stiff, hard to use double-action-only pistols. The LDA trigger has a long arc of movement with a relatively low level of resistance to pressure from the shooter's finger both through the stroke and, most critically, at the point of release. And the 7.45 still features the thumb safety and grip safety of the original 1911A1, making it easy to secure against unintended discharges, and fast into action from the holster. The incredibly accurate fully ramped, match-type barrel is also crowned and forged, something normally seen only on a custom 1911. The gun is very smoothly finished and its sight has deep lateral serrations.
I will ship UPS Ground for $30.
Payment : Certified Check, Money Order, PayPal
